

Day 8: AI for OSINT

## Introduction

Day 8 of my 30 Days of OSINT (Open Source Intelligence) Challenge.

Today, I explored Artificial Intelligence (AI) for Open Source Intelligence (OSINT)—one of the fastest-growing areas in cybersecurity and digital investigations.
OSINT traditionally involves collecting and analyzing publicly available information from websites,
social media, documents, search engines, maps, and other online sources. However, as the volume of publicly available data 
continues to grow, manually analyzing this information becomes increasingly difficult. AI helps investigators process large datasets,
identify patterns, summarize findings, automate repetitive tasks, and support faster decision-making.
It is important to understand that AI does not replace an OSINT investigator—it enhances their capabilities. 
Human verification, critical thinking, and ethical judgment remain essential throughout every investigation.


